		{"id":"196ef980cce4c839","type":"text","text":"## Meridian Building\nComplete writing the backstory of the [[Meridian Building]].","x":-3800,"y":800,"width":331,"height":160,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"ce50375c641ca90f","type":"text","text":"## Events & Dates\n- The world collapsed in 2000.\n- Twenty-five years had passed since civilization crumbled.","x":-4640,"y":800,"width":400,"height":180,"color":"#ff6600"},
		{"id":"0066cd536010cd14","type":"text","text":"## Chapter 3 Edits\nI've highlighted the section that needs more work. It should also explain more about [[Jason Chen]]'s past.\n\n*\"\"We can't save everyone,\" Jason said softly, but Raven heard the pain in his voice. It was the same pain she carried, the weight of all the people they couldn't help, all the horrors they had to witness in silence.\"*","x":-4220,"y":800,"width":400,"height":360,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"97b92fad7480340d","type":"text","text":"## Write the Missing Backstories\nIt's important to write the backstory of [[Ashveil]] before finishing the [[Chapter 3]].\n\nOther locations that need more information include:\n- [[Ashenfall]] and its building [[Meridian Building]]\n- [[Blackreach]]\n- [[Nerath]]\n\nMake sure to expand the backstory of the [[Financial District]] where the next chapters will take place.","x":-3440,"y":800,"width":460,"height":400},
		{"id":"1b449d77a990c695","type":"text","text":"## Feedback by my Editor\n\n- [ ] Fix the pace in [[Chapter 2]] line 132.\n- [ ] I haven't mentioned [[Jason Chen]] family. In [[Chapter 1]] it stops weird.\n- [ ] I need to fix the connection between [[Blackreach]] and [[Nerath]].","x":-2940,"y":800,"width":545,"height":280,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"ba09488949ee2725","type":"text","text":"## Description\n\nA book about an endless war between human beings. A ruined world, filled with strangers, each one with their own intensions.\n\nThere are two main characters, a young woman named [[Raven Martinez]] and a young guy called [[Jason Chen]]. The story takes place 25 years after the devastating events. Our two characters met by accident, and they spent a night together, hidden by the enemies inside an abandoned house at night, while raining.\n\nThey decide to travel together and help each other, and that's when their journey begins.","x":-2840,"y":-1160,"width":889,"height":318},
